They like having villains who are antithesis's to the hero, so having Black Goliath (Fishburne) be the villain would fit that mold.  1.) He can grow really big, which would make for some fun Godzilla like battles with Ant-Man in the city 3.) It would mean we would have one male villain and one female villain... a villain to line-up with each of our protagonists (Ant-Man & Wasp)  4.)  Fishburne is familiar with Pym's tech, which Ghost is using... 5.)  Nothing like a bait and switch on who the real villain is... get everyone thinking it is Ghost, and then flip the script and reveal it is Fisbhurne

text: (minor spoilers for Avengers: Infinity War)     My sister & I saw Avengers: Infinity Wars on opening day & it is AWESOME! I'm already predicting how Ant-Man & The Wasp will end. After Ant-Man & The Wasp complete their mission, they celibate at Hank Pym's house. Everything seems ok, but then Hope says "Guys...something is wrong with me". Hank says "Are you ok", Hank recoils back in shock when he sees her dissolve into nothingness. Before Hank can say anything Scott says "you're hand". Hank looks at his dissolving hand, then he dissolves completely. Scott is sitting in shock, he's brought back to reality when his phone rings. He looks at the caller-id, sees its his daughter. Scott says "Hi Cassie". Cassie says "Get over here quick". Scott says "What's wrong". Cassie says "Mommy disappeared in front of me". Scott puts 2 seemingly unrelated things together. Scott says "Stay right there, I'll be there as soon as I can". Scott races over to where his daughter lives. He sees that many vehicles are not even moving, some have even crashed into something. Scott finally arrives at his ex-wife house. Scott knocks on the door, door gets flung open & Cassie hugs her father. Scott says "What happened", Cassie responds "I don't know. Mommy disappered, its like when you put Alka-Seltzer in water". Scott picks up Cassie, looks around & says "What's going on". Then the movie cuts to black & the credits roll.

text: This movie is for me one of the best MCU movies. Itâ€™s not trying to be anything huge and revolutionary, but itâ€™s not trying to be a classic hero versus villain story either. This movie is more about many people with different problems intercepting, which turns into conflict or resolution (Ant-Man with house arrest, Ghost with her phasing problem, Hank and Wasps need to rescue Janet, Sonny Birch and his mission to get Quantum tech on the black market and into the future for consumers, etc.). Besides that, the comedy was golden, the action was fun and kinetic, the characters were great (including new additions), and pairing of Ant-Man and the Wasp was just perfect. I guess you can say *it takes two to make a thing go right* indeed. Ghost was one of the most sympathetic yet tragic antagonists of the MCU, who also uses her phasing abilities to make some of the best and most creative scenes. In fact, the only thing that makes her a villain and not an antihero are the desperate measures she will go to to survive. Sheâ€™s very complex and tragic, and keeps the streak of great MCU villains going. Also, those end credits scenes were great, and neatly set up Ant-Man in a way for Avengers 4 next year. Who else thought this movie was amazing?

text: WARNING this review may contain spoilers read at you're own risk. This is another great addition to the MCU. we now learn in this movie why Ant-Man was not in infinity war and he had a good reason. a lot of people were wondering how this movie was going to fit in and they pulled it off. first off let's talk about the movie, this movie is fantastic but I think the first one was a little bit better. Let's Talk about Ghost. Was she really a bad guy? some would say yes because of the motives and lengths she would have taken to complete that motive, like killing and kidnapping(Don't want to give too much away) would make her a villain. but some would say no because she had a good reason. I would say yes. yes to the motive and lengths that she would have taken to accomplish it but all in all, she was a villain, but if it wasn't for her reason or extreme motives and lengths then she would not be a villain. to be honest I thought she sucked as a bad guy now that I think of it she was a pretty good villain. Not every good villain has to take over the world. but killing someone to save your own life is pretty villainous. like I said I don't want to give away too much let's just say that she was going to sacrifice a character to save her self that hank just found out was still alive and is in the quantum realm, that's all I'm going to say. so yeah Ghost is a good villain. the acting, story and special effects are great in this movie all the actors did a great job in this film like always and it was well directed. the movie is also really funny there is this one scene where Ant-Man's suite starts glitching out in a school and it is hilarious. they also introduce Goliath in this movie which is cool but he plays only as his regular self as bill foster. the end credit scene is awesome. but I wonder where they are going with it. I have to talk about it so if you don't want to know quit reading. so the end credit scene shows that Scott is in the quantum realm getting stuff to help ghost to stabilize herself this is after they save Janet and Janet stabilizes ghost aka Ava, but when Scott goes into the quantum realm Janet, hope and hank dust away from when Thanos destroyed the gauntlet. so now Scott is stuck in the quantum realm he had to have someone help him get out. I was like wow what just happened. so now we know how this movie ties in. I really enjoyed this movie and I know you will too. this movie is cinematastic. if you have not seen this movie then I recommend you do one more thing Evangeline Lilly was an amazing Wasp she did such a great job at the character and I hope to see her in more MCU you just canâ€™t bring in a bad ass character like that then dust her away. But I'm glad that Wasp made it to the big screen I'm pretty sure she will be back cause I'm pretty sure Ant-Man is going to have a third movie, oh and i forgot about this second bad guy that wasp has a dealing with he is a black market gangster named Sonny Burch which just gets in the way he also wants the lab. his character is not bad, but comical and Micheal Pena is hilarious as ever. rating 5/5

text: Everything with this movie was great. Great special effects, great casting (well it's the same cast as in the first one) and acting, solid special effects, great pacing, fun action scenes, overall a great MCU movie. Except for the plot, it sucks, plain a simple. A lot of the subplots and the motivation behind what the characters do and how things work and end up just made no sense, to me it's Thor Dark World all over again. And yes I'm being a bit nitpicky on this one because I held Marvel movies at a significantly higher standards after their amazing work with Civil War, Thor Ragnarok, Black Panther and Avengers, Ant Man and The Wasp is a good movie, but not anywhere near the quality of Marvel's recent movies.
